CONTEXT
Here is a multiple-choice question in JSON format.
{
    "question": "Assume that the table below is delivered to you as a CSV file. Which of the potential solutions would load the data into a DataFrame object where the index is set to the month column?\n\n\ntickets_monthly.csv\n```\n   month  opened  resolved  rejected  people_involved\n    Jan    1098       776        81               12\n    Feb    1266       910        78               13\n    Mar    1419       954       126               12\n    Apr    1229       829        89               13\n    May    1106       811        74               13\n    Jun    1166       859        50               12\n    Jul    1132       864        80               13\n    Aug    1083       726        99               12\n    Sep    1018       761        43               10\n    Oct    1434       964       155               13\n    Nov    1283       935       101                9\n    Dec    1335       978        80               14\n```",
    "choices": [
        {
            "choice": "`pd.read_csv(\"tickets_monthly.csv\", index=0)`",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "`pd.read_csv(\"tickets_monthly\", index_col=0)`",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "`pd.read_csv(\"tickets_monthly.csv\", index_col=0)`",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "`df = pd.read_csv(\"tickets_monthly.csv\", index_col=0)`",
            "correct": "true"
        },
        {
            "choice": "`df = pd.read_csv(\"tickets_monthly.csv\", index='month')`",
            "correct": "false"
        }
    ]
}

Evaluate the above question based on the principles that are used to evaluate multiple-choice questions.
